unt": 47, "timestamp": "2024-01-23T12:19:13.000Z", "childPosts": [], "ownerUsername": "cleaning_biz_growth_academy", "ownerId": "53463611699", "productType": "clips", "isCommentsDisabled": false}, {"id": "3286225469144925549", "type": "Video", "shortCode": "C2bBKcsOYVt", "caption": "Here are 3 ways to step away from cleaning and maintain quality...\n\nThe biggest fear about us stepping away from the cleaning from us and our clients is always about quality!\n\nSo how do we maintain quality while stepping away...\n\n\ud83d\udcda Create an evolving training program, continue to educate yourself so you can continue to better your team and your service to your clients...\n\n\ud83d\udde3\ufe0f Master the art of communicating your expectations to your team, and also making sure that your team understands your expectations. Just because we communicate something doesn't mean it is understood.\n\n\ud83d\udccbCreate inspections and spend time with your team or have a supervisor that spends time with your team inspecting, coaching and retraining when necessary...\n\nThere is a lot more that goes into running and managing a team for your cleaning business, but implementing these three steps could help outdooring your growing stages!\n\nComment \"QUALITY\" if you need help stepping away in 2024\n\n#cleaningcommunity\n#cleaningbusiness\n#CleaningBusinessSuccess\n#Cleanpreneurship\n#janitorialcleaningservice", "hashtags": ["cleaningcommunity", "cleaningbusiness", "CleaningBusinessSuccess", "Cleanpreneurship", "janitorialcleaningservice"], "mentions": [], "url": "https://www.instagram.com/p/C2bBKcsOYVt/", "commentsCount": 1, "dimensionsHeight": 852, "dimensionsWidth": 480, "displayUrl": "https://instagram.flas1-1.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t51.71878-15/503291877_740826405048458_8066292545838693548_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_e15_tt6&_nc_ht=instagram.flas1-1.fna.fbcdn.net&_nc_cat=102&_nc_oc=Q6cZ2gGwFhZyi0KKTMsl2HpfVGbvlPlmi5ngb3f3lPqRPIbilvd57weVsOTH1YaeXiJEb1c&_nc_ohc=8xB2xZ-fI8QQ7kNvwF9LcmT&_nc_gid=YWV